collation.p:
The manuscript comprises 26 quires, the majority gatherings of 10 leaves (Quires 7-19) or 8 leaves (Quires 21-26). Quires 1 and 20 were added in the 15th century. Quire 2 comprises two leaves, but they do not obviously form a bifolium; f. iv may once have been conjoint with what is now the front pastedown - both the front pastedown and f. iv recto are hair-sides - but the addition of Quire 1 means that the structure of Quire 2 remains uncertain. The manuscript has previously been collated, with quire numbers written in pencil in the lower right-hand corner, starting at '1' on Quire 3. Folio numbers were written, apparently around the same time, on the first leaf of the second half of each quire. The tightness of the binding means that the following collation formulae are reliant on these earlier notations.
Quire 14 (ff. i, [i a], ii-iii; added in the 15th century) ;
Quire 2two (ff. iv-v)
Quires 3-58 (ff. 1-24)
Quire 612 (ff. 25-36)
Quires 7-1910 (ff. 37-166) ;
Quire 204 (ff. 167-170; added in the 15th century) ;
Quires 21-268 (ff. 171-218)
